                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-green-50 border border-green-200 px-4 py-3">
                          <span class="font-semibold text-green-700">Yes \u2192</span>
                          <span class="text-gray-700 ml-2">{step.yes}</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3">
                          <span class="font-semibold text-gray-500">No \u2192</span>
                          <span class="text-gray-600 ml-2">{step.no === 'continue' ? 'go to next question' : step.no}</span>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </section>

          <section id="hybrid">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-5">8. Hybrid architectures (combining technologies)</h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              Four common hybrid patterns at scale. Each uses two or three technologies at different phases of the workflow \u2014 no forced &quot;one technology only&quot; constraint.
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
